FIX YOUR FORM: LEG PRESS ❌✅

Please SAVE for future reference + RESHARE to support my content.🙏🏼🙏🏼❤️

Firstly, what other exercises did you need a form breakdown on like this?🤔

Leg press is one of my favourite lower body exercises. Depending on your foot placement and positioning you can hit more quads, Glutes/hamstrings, adductors etc.

Common mistakes:

❌Lower back rounding at the bottom
❌Butt lifted off seat
❌Too much depth. When you are using too large a range of motion it’s shifting the tension from your Glutes to your lower back.
❌Knees caving!
❌Forcefully locking out knees at the top of each rep. You are placing a lot of tension on your knee joints which is taking is away from your muscles.

Form tips:

✅Keep slight bend in knees (stop just short of locking them out)
✅Knees track out in line with toes. Consciously think about ‘knees out’ if you find they buckle in under heavy weight.
✅Lower back is flush to the seat. Grab the handles and pull your butt/back down!
✅Staying within range of motion: not too shallow and not too deep.

I hope this was helpful. Let me know! 🙏🏼🤓

How to get your first PULL UP! 🔥READ 👇🏼

When I first started out in the gym a goal of mine was to do 1 unassisted pull up!!! I was once a beginner to and now I can do many!! 🏆

There are stages of progression that can work through:

👉🏼Eccentric only (negatives) pull ups: Here we focus only on the lowering phase. Use a bench to jump up into position & then slowly lower yourself down.

👉🏼Band assisted - around feet.  Assistance by a band in this position allows it to be easier from the bottom. The band is stretched most in this position so has greater ability to assist with each rep.

👉🏼Band assisted - around knees. Having the band around your knees provides less help from the bottom. Try get a few bands of varying thickness so you can decrease the resistance as you get stronger. As you build strength you will be able to lessen the amount of resistance you use until you can do them on your own!!

👉🏼Body weight: Focus on pulling your shoulder blacks back and pulling the bar down with each rep. I imagine pulling my elbows to the floor. If you can only do one rep…try doing 3 sets of one rep. Next week try add an additional rep.

💪🏼Aside from the progression with the actual exercise itself…remember to work on building your overall upper body strength! The stronger you are…the easier and faster your progress will be.

I hope this video helps!! 💗

FIX YOUR FORM: LAT PULLDOWN ❌✅ 

Please SAVE for future reference + RESHARE to support my content. 🙏🏼❤️

When I put up a questions box asking for what you needed help with… upper body exercises technique was high on the request list!

Lat pulldown is a very common upper body exercise targeting your lats/upper back, which for most is ‘basic’ but I still see so many form issues! 🥵

Common mistakes:

❌Putting bar down too low. You don’t need to be pulling down past your chest to your waist. With this exercise more range is not best!
❌Using too much momentum. You don’t need to swing back and use as much momentum to pull the weight. If you want to isolate and engage the right muscles you need strict form.
❌Leaning too far back.
❌Grip too wide. You don’t need to grip all the way at the ends of the bar!

Form tips:

✅Pull bar down to the top of chest/just below chin.
✅Keep forearm as vertical as possible.
✅Drive elbows down
✅Keep chest/torso up with your core braced
✅Use a mid width grip. You should be holding just outside should width.
💪🏼Control the movement

I hope this helped! ✨

node.text:
DITCH THE BAR PAD WHEN SQUATTING!! 👋🏻

You don’t need it.

🥵Having this cushioned pad around the bar makes it unstable on your back. It’s the same reason why we don’t want to squat in spoungy shoes. You want stability.

🥵The bar sitting off your back just that little bit can throw off your bar path. This will be a lot more noticeable the heavier you squat.

🥵The pad impacts how you can create tightness with your upper back. It’s big and bulky. You won’t be able to pull the bar down tight enough and get your shoulders/elbows into position.

❌ The bar shouldn’t be sitting up too high on your neck, resting on vertebrae. This is what is likely causing pain. 🥵

✅Instead - have the bar sitting a little further down and resting along your traps.

Hold the bar as narrow as you can while squeezing your shoulder blades back tight and then lifting your elbows high (as I show in the video). You also want to keep your chest up.

💡This upper back tightness creates a ‘shelf’ for the bar to rest on. This is your cushion - you don’t need a bar pad. 💪🏼

✨If you are just starting out...squatting for the first time ever and feel more comfortable and confident initially with the pad - that’s okay. Soon enough it will be time to ditch the pad and focus on correct technique so you can progress in weight too! ✨

SAVE THE BAR PAD FOR HIP THRUSTS👏🏼👏🏼👏🏼

BISCOFF BANANA FRENCH TOAST 🍌🍪 Tag a Biscoff lover!

French toast is always a breakfast favourite among the LSF community and since you all have been obsessing over Biscoff lately here is another recipe incorporating it.🤤

Let me know if you make it!

2 slices wholemeal bread
1 egg
1/3 cup almond milk
1/2 tsp vanilla extract
1/4 tsp cinnamon
1/4 tbsp sugar free maple syrup
1 tbsp biscoff spread (melted)
1/3 banana (thinly sliced)
Cooking spray

In a medium sized bowl - whisk together egg, almond milk, vanilla extract, cinnamon and maple syrup.
Add bread slices into the bowl and allows to soak up the mixture for 1 minute on each side of the bread.
Spray cooking spray into a fry pan over medium heat.
Once the pan is hot, add bread slices into the pan. Before flipping sides add a few banana slices on top.
Cook for 2-3 minutes on each side or until golden.
Top with biscoff spread and banana.
To melt the biscoff put it in the microwave for 1 minute.

ENJOY QUEENS. 💕

APPROX MACROS
Calories: 395
P: 12 F: 15 C: 53

GLUTE WORKOUT + A DOSE OF EDUCATION 🍑🍑🍑🤓

Please make sure to SAVE it really helps my content keep popping up in the IG feed.🙏🏼🙏🏼🥺❤️

I know there are a lot of workouts floating around instagram but I do hope you read my captions when I go into more details on exercises. This will help you actually LEARN more about what you are doing.💪🏼✨

A1) LEG PRESS FEET HIGH 3x 10 as 1 & 1/4 rep. Feet high is targeting your glutes in their lengthened position. The quarter is added into the bottom where your glutes are under the most amount of tension. Remember to keep yourself pulled down into the sear & no rounding of back.

A2) BACK EXTENSION 3x 10 weighted + 10 body weight. Holding the weight out higher in front of you as opposed to close on your chest will make this exercise harder.

B1) HIGH STEP UP 3x 10. Focus on the front leg on the box doing all the work and the back leg as little as possible. I hinge over at the hips to increase the stretch in the glute.

B2) SINGLE LEG HIP THRUST 3x 12 as 1 & 1/4. One of the most savage body weight only exercises.

C1) BACK FOOT ELEVATED RDL 3x 10. Single leg exercise however the back leg is up on the bench for support. I like to do these with a slower tempo to increase TUT.

C2) CABLE KICBACK 1 & 1/4 3x 10.
C3) CABLE STRAIGHT LEG ABDUCTION 3X 10 as 1 & 1/4.

This was an exact workout of mine prelockdown.💪🏼❤️
Let me know what you think if you give this a go.

‼️‼️p.s. for all my girls training at HOME right now I have a HOME WORKOUT LIVE SCHEDULE on my IG stories. 🏡💪🏼

THURSDAY, FRIDAY + SATURDAY 8AM AEST.‼️‼️🥳🥳🥳

node.text:
STOP OBSESSING OVER CALORIES BURNED ON YOUR FITNESS TRACKERS‼️

❌Please do not base what you eat around  the calories burned on your watch.
❌Please do not look think you need to eat back calories burned.

There have been many studies to show that activity trackers are NOT consistently accurate/reliable as a measure of energy expenditure.

I know so many of you out there rely on these numbers to justify whether your workout was good or not…whether it was effective…and often feel like it was a waste of time or a failure if a certain number on your watch wasn’t hit.

1) Burning a number of calories shouldn’t be your #1 goal of a workout.
2) As a coach that number doesn’t impact the programming in the gym.

I wear an activity tracker (FitBit) but the only thing I use it for are steps and sleep.

Fitness trackers are highly inaccurate and all fitness trackers would give you different numbers. They simply don’t have enough accurate data about you to make an informed reading. ⚠️

Simply doing a workout to burn a number of calories is not a good mindset to have long term and it takes the enjoyment out of this lifestyle.

There are far better ways to track during out workouts such as the weight used in the gym for your lifts, improvements in technique, how exercise makes you feel, the mental health benefits etc. Track your progress to get stronger!💪🏼💪🏼💪🏼👏🏼

REMEMBER: THESE INACCURATE NUMBERS SHOULDN’T MAKE YOU FEEL BAD ABOUT A WORKOUT!✨

HOW TO: SPLIT SQUAT ❌✅🔥🔥front & side view.

SAVE + RESHARE if it was helpful !🙏🏼 

Split squats are a staple in both mine & my client programs. It’s a love/hate relationship for me. 🥵There are many variations, even by adding elevation for front foot, back foot etc it can recruit muscles in different ways. You can do them body weight only, hold dumbbells, a barbell, plus incorporate different methods like pauses, 1 & 1/4 reps etc to ramp up the intensity.🔥👊🏼

🎯The goal here is to drive that front knee forward to maximise knee flexion. This also makes it a more quad dominant exercise. Yes it is okay for your knee to travel past your toes! 👏🏼👏🏼
 Don’t let your knee cave in! This is very common & often why lunges/split squats can result in knee pain. Make sure to turn your toes out slightly and keep your knee tracking out in line with it.

‼️Here are some brief coaching cues to think about when doing this exercise:

Drop back knee down toward the floor.
Push front knee forwards.
Front foot should be turned out slightly.
Knee tracks in line with toes - Don’t let knee cave in!!!
Think ‘hamstring to calf’ when travelling forward.
Front foot should be flat to floor.
Back leg heel up.
Core braced.
Shoulders back/upright torso.

I hope this helps! 🤓❤️
@laurensimpsonfitness

node.text:
What are your non-negotiables for this week? 💕🌈🌻

Whenever I want to get back on track or be really focused on a goal (whether it be shredding, building, or just maintaining) the secret lies within getting MOMENTUM.

✨Take each day as it comes.✨

Here is the current list I make myself every morning - that I then reflect on everything night.

🍎Stick to my meal plan
👟Step goal: 12,000 minimum
💪🏼Workout
💧2L+ water
🎧1 podcast min
😴6.5hours min sleep

The more good days you have - you get on a roll. The days accumulate. There is a huge sense of satisfaction with ticking off things you achieve that helps with building good habits.

Now let’s be real…that first week is always tough. You may feel hungry, you may feel sore, you may feel a little more tired than usual…BUT every day TICK OFF that list. You’ll see me at night time checking off my list to keep me accountable.

If you had a sh*tty week last week I encourage you to just focusing on each day ahead right now. Start with small changes and build momentum.

SO, WRITE IT DOWN AND TICK IT OFF THIS WEEK QUEENS! ✍🏻✨🌈

COMMON DEADLIFT MISTAKES ❌⚠️🆘

Please SAVE & RESHARE if this was helpful 🙏🏼

Here are a few deadlift mistakes I commonly see as a coach.

⚠️ HYPEREXTENDING THE LOCKOUT 
You do not need to excessively thrust forward & lean back to lockout your deadlift.

Butt squeeze here isn’t building your glutes girls! Your glutes are actually under zero tension at the top - if anything you are just engaging your lower back which is not want you want here!

✅ Just stand up straight. Neutral spine and hips in extension. Slight glute squeeze is fine - just don’t overdo it.

⚠️ BAR STARTING TO FAR AWAY.
When you are starting with your feet too far away from the bar this actually makes deadlifting harder due to the bar path (increases horizontal moment arm). This can also put pressure on your spine. 🥴

✅ Make sure you start with the bar right up at your shins. The bar should remain close to your body right from the start. Bar path should be straight up and down. 

🥵 ROUNDING THE UPPER BACK
It’s common to see upper back rounding as a result of zero tension being created with your shoulder blades and lats. There is no tightness. When your upper back begins to round, tension moves away from your glutes/hammies to back.

✅From the starting position keep your shoulder blades pulled back and down. Your lats should be engaged, bar pulled tight in toward your body. Spine should be kept neutral.

⚠️NO RESET, USING MOMENTUM & FORM BREAKING DOWN.

Now ‘touch and go’ reps are not bad however I do recommend to slow down your reps and reset at the bottom of every rep if your goal is to continue working on your form and build strength.

✅Resetting each rep can make sure your body has max tension (eg resetting upper back tension), your form isn’t breaking down, and every rep is pulled from a solid foundation. It’s also better for building up strength out of the bottom as you are pulling from a complete stop - you aren’t relying on the ‘bouncing’.

I hope this video helped. Let me know ❤️

A few random thoughts & facts 💁🏼‍♀️💕✨

All dressed up here with no where to go. 🔒Currently in Sydney lockdown. End of week 3. My DM is flooded with messages saying they love ‘Lockdown Loz’ more than ever… I guess i’ll take that compliment.😂🤷🏼‍♀️

My Starbucks order: long black ‘americano’ with sugar free vanilla or caramel syrup.

My Ugg’s boots are life. I have even done a few workouts in them at home lately 😜

I’m forever cold. Mark teases me that my hands are always freezing…even when I’m doing a workout. I also very rarely sweat. 🙃

Unpopular opinion: I like pickles on cheeseburgers and pineapple on pizza.

I can buy a whole block of chocolate and literally just eat ONE square and be satisfied….but chips I have zero self control.🥵

If I could travel anywhere in the world right now it would be back to Europe. Greek islands & Ibiza 🌴🌍

I am the worst at texting back. It’s either instantly or in days. Soz 😩😂🤪 My friends know I love them to death. ❤️😇

Grocery shopping is weirdly therapeutic.

My favourite subjects at school were English & Ancient History. Least favourite - maths.

I’m scared of roller coasters and all thrill seeking rides. 😩😭 Mark has forced me on many with him at Disney Land & Movie World 😂

I hate scary movies. Fantasy or Rom Coms are my fav. 👏🏼

💕💫 Sending love & positive vibes to you all this weekend.
